segment.source: The Administrators node is one level below the Application Virtualization System node in the Scope pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console.
segment.target: The Administrators node is one level below the Application Virtualization System node in the Scope pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console.

segment.source: When you select this node, the Results pane displays a list of administrator groups.
segment.target: When you select this node, the Results pane displays a list of administrator groups.

segment.source: Right-click the Administrators node to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.
segment.target: Right-click the Administrators node to display a pop-up menu that contains the following elements.

segment.source: Add Administrator Group
segment.target: Add Administrator Group

segment.source: Displays the Select Groups dialog to find and add the desired administrator group.
segment.target: Displays the Select Groups dialog to find and add the desired administrator group.

segment.source: Click Finish to add the group.
segment.target: Click Finish to add the group.

segment.source: Opens a new management console with the selected node as the root node.
segment.target: Opens a new management console with the selected node as the root node.
